ZH: 他喜欢在别人做事的时候添乱。
EN: He likes to create chaos when others are working.

ZH: 不要在我写论文的时候添乱。
EN: Don't disturb me while I'm writing my thesis.

ZH: 别让他进来，他只会添乱。
EN: Don't let him in, he will only make trouble.

ZH: 请不要添乱，我们正在紧张地讨论。
EN: Please don't disrupt, we are having an intense discussion.

ZH: 他故意添乱，试图破坏我们的计划。
EN: He deliberately creates chaos, trying to sabotage our plan.

ZH: 他的行为总是添乱，没人想和他一起工作。
EN: His behavior always causes chaos, no one wants to work with him.

ZH: 他们的意见总是互相添乱，让我们进展缓慢。
EN: Their opinions always confuse each other, making our progress slow.

ZH: 你不要在这个重要会议上添乱。
EN: Please don't disrupt the important meeting.

ZH: 请不要在考试的时候添乱。
EN: Please don't distract during the exam.

ZH: 他总是跳来跳去添乱。
EN: He is always jumping around and causing chaos.

ZH: 别让他参与这个项目，他肯定会添乱。
EN: Don't let him be involved in this project, he will surely create chaos.

ZH: 他喜欢添乱然后看着大家为此陷入混乱。
EN: He likes to create chaos and watch everyone get confused.

ZH: 我希望大家能够专注，不要添乱。
EN: I hope everyone can focus and not cause any disruptions.

ZH: 不要总是添乱，让我们按部就班地进行。
EN: Don't always create chaos, let's proceed step by step.

ZH: 当你感到无聊时，请不要添乱。
EN: When you feel bored, please don't create chaos.

ZH: 我们不能让一个人添乱影响整个团队的进展。
EN: We cannot allow one person's disruption to affect the progress of the whole team.

ZH: 请不要添乱，这是一个非常重要的任务。
EN: Please don't cause chaos, this is a very important task.

ZH: 每个人都应该尽量避免添乱，尽力保持秩序。
EN: Everyone should try to avoid causing chaos and strive to maintain order.

ZH: 如果你不对计划满意，可以提出改进的建议，但不要添乱。
EN: If you're not satisfied with the plan, you can suggest improvements, but please don't disrupt.

ZH: 在一个团队中，每个人都有责任不添乱，共同完成目标。
EN: In a team, everyone has the responsibility not to create chaos and work together to achieve the goals.
